# State Management Guidelines

## React State Patterns
- Use `useState` for component-level state
- Group related state variables when they change together
- Use descriptive state variable names that indicate their purpose

## Loading States
- Always implement loading states for async operations
- Disable interactive elements during loading
- Provide visual feedback with loading text or spinners
- Reset loading state in both success and error cases

## Error Handling
- Use dedicated error state variables
- Clear errors when starting new operations
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log detailed errors to console for debugging

## Form State
- Validate inputs before submission
- Clear previous errors when starting new operations
- Handle keyboard events (Enter key) for better UX
- Use controlled components with value and onChange props

## Async Operations Pattern
```typescript
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

const handleAsyncOperation = async () => {
  setIsLoading(true);
  setError(null);
  
  try {
    // Async operation
  } catch (err) {
    setError('User-friendly error message');
    console.error('Detailed error:', err);
  } finally {
    setIsLoading(false);
  }
};
```